attributeList.attribute: INTerAction database (IntAct) provides an open source database and toolkit for the storage, presentation and analysis of molecular interactions.
European Bioinformatics Institute; Wellcome Trust Genome Campus; Hinxton, Cambridge; CB10 1SD; United Kingdom
A collection of literature-mined stable and functionally defined human molecular complexes of known stoichiometry and biological role.

secondaryRef.secondary: positive regulation of mitotic metaphase/anaphase transition
positive regulation of anaphase-promoting complex-dependent catabolic process

attributeList.attribute: Acts at the spindle checkpoint in a surveillance mechanism that mediates a delay in the onset of anaphase until all chromosomes are properly attached to the mitotic or meiotic spindle by inhibiting the anaphase-promoting complex (CPX-760), an E3 ubquitin ligase complex required for onset of anaphase. The Mitotic checkpoint complex is a more potent inhibitor of the APC/C than Mad2-Cdc20 alone (CPX-962).
